WEBVTT

00:00:00.620 --> 00:00:03.620
Welcome to our program.

00:00:03.620 --> 00:00:07.620
Here's a preview of what we can look forward to.

00:00:07.620 --> 00:00:10.619
This brother began his ministry in the Congo

00:00:10.619 --> 00:00:13.619
when his fellow witnesses were few in number.

00:00:13.619 --> 00:00:18.620
How did Jehovah bless his hard work to preach and shepherd?

00:00:18.620 --> 00:00:21.620
It's a joy when we come together at assembly halls

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:23.620
for spiritual programs.

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:25.620
But how much work goes into caring

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:28.620
for these places of pure worship?

00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:31.620
We also work to maintain peaceful relationships

00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:33.619
with our brothers and sisters.

00:00:33.619 --> 00:00:35.619
What lesson does this sister learn

00:00:35.619 --> 00:00:39.619
that lets her see the beautiful qualities and others?

00:00:39.619 --> 00:00:42.619
And we'll consider the privilege we have

00:00:42.619 --> 00:00:44.619
to be fellow workers with God.

00:00:44.619 --> 00:00:48.619
You're watching the October 2017 edition

00:00:48.619 --> 00:00:50.619
of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:50.619 --> 00:01:12.790
We begin with a report from the United States branch

00:01:12.790 --> 00:01:14.790
in Wal-Kill, New York.

00:01:15.790 --> 00:01:17.790
Any Bethel assignment is a joy

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.790
and sometimes a challenge.

00:01:20.790 --> 00:01:23.790
Proper training is therefore an important part

00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:25.790
of every job.

00:01:25.790 --> 00:01:28.790
How does the maintenance department train hundreds

00:01:28.790 --> 00:01:32.790
of volunteers to work efficiently and safely?

00:01:32.790 --> 00:01:34.790
And how do the students feel

00:01:34.790 --> 00:01:43.870
about the practical training they receive?

00:01:43.870 --> 00:01:46.870
There were a few factors that created the need

00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:50.870
at Bethel for a more structured training program.

00:01:50.870 --> 00:01:52.870
One of those factors included

00:01:52.870 --> 00:01:55.870
the regular changeover in personnel.

00:01:55.870 --> 00:01:57.870
The brothers have to be more versatile.

00:01:57.870 --> 00:01:59.870
In their assignments, they may have to do tasks.

00:01:59.870 --> 00:02:01.870
They previously weren't trained on.

00:02:01.870 --> 00:02:04.870
Printing equipment became more technologically advanced.

00:02:04.870 --> 00:02:08.870
Our building systems became more complicated.

00:02:08.870 --> 00:02:11.870
Computer systems were now starting to be used

00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:13.870
to control virtually everything.

00:02:13.870 --> 00:02:16.870
I feel like Bethel has definitely always been good

00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:19.870
about training, but especially now,

00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:21.870
I think everyone sees the need to continue investing

00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:23.870
in the brothers and sisters

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:25.870
that are currently at Bethel.

00:02:25.870 --> 00:02:27.870
I don't think it's possible for someone

00:02:27.870 --> 00:02:30.870
to know less about the trades than I did when I started.

00:02:30.870 --> 00:02:33.870
I remember my first reaction when I was invited

00:02:33.870 --> 00:02:36.870
to help an electrical was a fear.

00:02:36.870 --> 00:02:38.870
So when I received my assignment,

00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:41.870
I found out that it involved

00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:43.870
running the heavy equipment.

00:02:43.870 --> 00:02:44.870
So I called my parents.

00:02:44.870 --> 00:02:46.870
I was really excited about it.

00:02:46.870 --> 00:02:48.870
I said, Mom and Dad, I guess what I get to do?

00:02:48.870 --> 00:02:52.870
And Dad says, OK, son, well,

00:02:52.870 --> 00:02:55.870
did you tell them that you don't know how to drive?

00:02:55.870 --> 00:02:59.870
It was decided to pull a group of highly experienced,

00:02:59.870 --> 00:03:03.870
highly skilled brothers to concentrate on developing

00:03:03.870 --> 00:03:06.870
and teaching repeatable, consistent classes

00:03:06.870 --> 00:03:10.870
that could bring people skill levels up to what was needed.

00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:13.870
We teach well over 100 different classes

00:03:13.870 --> 00:03:15.870
in 12 major categories.

00:03:15.870 --> 00:03:18.870
Here at Bethel, I've probably been a part of

00:03:18.870 --> 00:03:20.870
over 30 different classes.

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:23.870
So it's been a variety depending on the needs

00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:24.870
at the time of the assignment.

00:03:24.870 --> 00:03:28.870
I would estimate that I've taken about 15 or 20

00:03:28.870 --> 00:03:30.870
different courses from safety and training

00:03:30.870 --> 00:03:33.870
over the course of my 13 years in learning a trade.

00:03:33.870 --> 00:03:34.870
I've become certified

00:03:34.870 --> 00:03:37.870
and at least these seven different license requirements.

00:03:37.870 --> 00:03:39.870
We teach people technical skills,

00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:42.870
but that's not the sole purpose of the training.

00:03:42.870 --> 00:03:44.870
If you aren't skilled in safety,

00:03:44.870 --> 00:03:46.870
you can't be skilled in your trade and vice versa.

00:03:46.870 --> 00:03:49.870
The objective in all of our safety courses

00:03:49.870 --> 00:03:52.870
is to get them to view safety the same way

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:55.870
Jehovah views it as a reflection of their spirituality.

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:58.870
So training and safety is essential.

00:03:58.870 --> 00:04:01.870
So our goal is to take them into the classroom,

00:04:01.870 --> 00:04:04.870
give them some time to consider the theoretical,

00:04:04.870 --> 00:04:06.870
and then we take them out where there's a lab setup

00:04:06.870 --> 00:04:08.870
and we have them do some tests on it.

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:11.870
Typically they will tell us that they've been able to learn

00:04:11.870 --> 00:04:14.870
more in a week than what they have learned

00:04:14.870 --> 00:04:16.870
in a year of trade school.

00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:20.870
We've done over 60,000 instances of training.

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:22.870
And so now receiving this training,

00:04:22.870 --> 00:04:28.870
it provides an area or an aspect in which I can give my 100% to Jehovah.

00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:32.870
You see it in their eyes are just so happy that they now have

00:04:32.870 --> 00:04:35.870
maybe a new skill or a new understanding

00:04:35.870 --> 00:04:38.870
that they can use to benefit Jehovah.

00:04:38.870 --> 00:04:40.870
I love the fact that I came into Bethel

00:04:40.870 --> 00:04:42.870
with virtually no experience,

00:04:42.870 --> 00:04:45.870
and not only did I receive a trade that I could use

00:04:45.870 --> 00:04:49.870
to carry out a work that glorifies Jehovah,

00:04:49.870 --> 00:04:52.870
but I was trained well enough that I can share that with others

00:04:52.870 --> 00:04:54.870
and they can be trained to.

00:04:54.870 --> 00:04:57.870
Helping someone else to go from that feeling

00:04:57.870 --> 00:05:00.870
of not knowing anything to feeling productive

00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:02.870
and feeling like they're contributing

00:05:02.870 --> 00:05:04.870
is a real joy for me.

00:05:04.870 --> 00:05:07.870
And they can take what they learn wherever they go.

00:05:07.870 --> 00:05:09.870
The confidence that people leave with,

00:05:09.870 --> 00:05:12.870
once they've received that investment,

00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:14.870
it's confidence that they can carry out whatever assignment

00:05:14.870 --> 00:05:16.870
Jehovah has given them,

00:05:16.870 --> 00:05:18.870
and the confidence that Jehovah is going to train them

00:05:18.870 --> 00:05:20.870
for whatever's being asked of them.

00:05:20.870 --> 00:05:22.870
I think if younger brothers and sisters

00:05:22.870 --> 00:05:25.870
are trying to learn a skill so that they can come to Bethel,

00:05:25.870 --> 00:05:27.870
that's commendable,

00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:29.870
but more importantly is spirituality.

00:05:29.870 --> 00:05:31.870
Let Jehovah finish your training.

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:33.870
In regard to training, we're really only getting started.

00:05:33.870 --> 00:05:35.870
The training that we are getting

00:05:35.870 --> 00:05:38.870
in this system of things by Jehovah

00:05:38.870 --> 00:05:40.870
and especially related to safety

00:05:40.870 --> 00:05:43.870
is absolutely going to be vital in the New World.

00:05:43.870 --> 00:05:46.870
I can imagine the idea of being able to use

00:05:46.870 --> 00:05:48.870
some of the things I've learned to figure out

00:05:48.870 --> 00:05:50.870
how we can use the natural resources

00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:52.870
in a way without using them up.

00:05:52.870 --> 00:05:54.870
We know that we serve a God who is known

00:05:54.870 --> 00:05:56.870
as the grand instructor.

00:05:56.870 --> 00:05:59.870
So the things that we're teaching and training right now,

00:05:59.870 --> 00:06:01.870
it can only expand in the future.

00:06:01.870 --> 00:06:04.870
And as long as you let him train you,

00:06:04.870 --> 00:06:09.620
you're going to be all right.

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:11.620
Good training gives us confidence

00:06:11.620 --> 00:06:13.620
to do our best for Jehovah.

00:06:13.620 --> 00:06:15.620
That's true at Bethel,

00:06:15.620 --> 00:06:18.620
but also true in the field.

00:06:18.620 --> 00:06:21.620
Have you, though, ever felt alone in your assignment,

00:06:21.620 --> 00:06:25.620
even if, for just a few hours in the ministry,

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:28.620
for the Possean Bucanga

00:06:28.620 --> 00:06:31.620
may have felt that way early in his assignment.

00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:33.620
He was the first circuit overseer

00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:37.620
for all of what is now the Democratic Republic of Congo

00:06:37.620 --> 00:06:39.620
and the Republic of Congo.

00:06:39.620 --> 00:06:42.620
He traveled great distances to visit

00:06:42.620 --> 00:06:45.620
the few brothers throughout the territory.

00:06:45.620 --> 00:06:49.620
Listen to what encouraged him the most to keep going.

00:06:49.620 --> 00:06:55.540
In 1960, I was made a circuit overseer

00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.540
for the whole of Congo.

00:06:57.540 --> 00:07:02.980
I was so happy to receive this privilege.

00:07:02.980 --> 00:07:05.980
But I was shocked and scared.

00:07:05.980 --> 00:07:08.980
The assignment was huge.

00:07:08.980 --> 00:07:11.980
Congo is a vast country.

00:07:11.980 --> 00:07:15.980
I was afraid to go to places I didn't know.

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:18.980
I felt overwhelmed,

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:20.980
so I turned to Jehovah.

00:07:20.980 --> 00:07:25.360
Sometimes I had to go through savannas

00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:27.360
and across the jungle.

00:07:27.360 --> 00:07:30.360
There were wild animals.

00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.360
One day, I climbed up a tree

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:34.360
to find a place to sleep.

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:37.360
I tied myself to a branch with my bell.

00:07:37.360 --> 00:07:40.360
I was afraid I would be taken by a boa snake.

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:45.959
I was afraid of getting lost in the forest.

00:07:45.959 --> 00:07:49.959
Visiting the brothers was very difficult.

00:07:49.959 --> 00:07:52.959
Sometimes the journey took many days.

00:07:52.959 --> 00:07:54.959
I remember one day,

00:07:54.959 --> 00:07:57.959
I left my house to visit the brothers to encourage them.

00:07:57.959 --> 00:08:04.189
I left at 5.30 in the morning

00:08:04.189 --> 00:08:08.189
and I arrived at 7.30 that night.

00:08:08.189 --> 00:08:11.189
I had to push my bicycle through sand

00:08:11.189 --> 00:08:14.189
for up to 13 miles or even more.

00:08:14.189 --> 00:08:17.189
Other times, we traveled by truck.

00:08:17.189 --> 00:08:19.189
That was not easy.

00:08:19.189 --> 00:08:23.189
You had to climb on top of the truck.

00:08:23.189 --> 00:08:27.189
I had to hold on tight so as not to fall.

00:08:27.189 --> 00:08:30.189
Congregations, isolated groups

00:08:30.189 --> 00:08:33.190
were far away from one another.

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:37.190
There were no phones at that time either.

00:08:37.190 --> 00:08:40.190
Even though they did not know I was coming,

00:08:40.190 --> 00:08:44.759
they made me feel so welcome.

00:08:44.759 --> 00:08:48.759
The brothers were really very hospitable.

00:08:48.759 --> 00:08:52.759
When I arrived, I was exhausted

00:08:52.759 --> 00:08:55.759
but so happy to see the brothers.

00:08:55.759 --> 00:09:02.029
The kids of Wala was a religion.

00:09:02.029 --> 00:09:05.029
They sent many letters to the Belgian branch

00:09:05.029 --> 00:09:08.029
to be recognized as Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:09:08.029 --> 00:09:13.539
These people used our publications

00:09:13.539 --> 00:09:16.539
and used the name Watchtower.

00:09:16.539 --> 00:09:20.539
It created a lot of confusion.

00:09:20.539 --> 00:09:23.539
To clarify the matter,

00:09:23.539 --> 00:09:26.539
the organization prepared a booklet.

00:09:26.539 --> 00:09:33.330
My mission was to check whether there were any genuine Jehovah's Witnesses

00:09:33.330 --> 00:09:34.330
in Kisangani.

00:09:34.330 --> 00:09:43.710
We found out that these people were not Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:09:43.710 --> 00:09:48.710
In all the confusion, people even tried to kill me during the trip.

00:09:48.710 --> 00:09:54.179
Fortunately, I managed to escape.

00:09:54.179 --> 00:10:00.230
Since it was Jehovah who assigned me this privilege,

00:10:00.230 --> 00:10:03.230
I was confident that he would always help me.

00:10:03.230 --> 00:10:11.779
And today, I am very happy to have at my side my children,

00:10:11.779 --> 00:10:14.779
my grandchildren, and my great-grandchildren,

00:10:14.779 --> 00:10:17.779
all Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:10:17.779 --> 00:10:22.289
Jehovah has given me many blessings.

00:10:22.289 --> 00:10:25.289
I am truly grateful.

00:10:25.289 --> 00:10:30.289
What a joy to be used by Almighty God.

00:10:30.289 --> 00:10:34.289
Through all these years, I have never lacked anything.

00:10:34.289 --> 00:10:39.629
Jehovah has given me this strength to serve him up until now

00:10:39.629 --> 00:10:43.629
to the age of 86.

00:10:43.629 --> 00:10:47.629
In everything and for everything,

00:10:47.629 --> 00:10:51.629
my trust really is in Jehovah.

00:10:51.629 --> 00:10:55.629
There were 46 publishers in the whole of Congo.

00:10:55.629 --> 00:11:05.769
Today, I hear there are more than 223,000 Jehovah's Witnesses in the Congo.

00:11:05.769 --> 00:11:14.610
Today, when I see the increase of Jehovah's People,

00:11:14.610 --> 00:11:19.559
to me, it is like a miracle.

00:11:19.559 --> 00:11:23.559
I thank Jehovah for allowing me to see the little one

00:11:23.559 --> 00:11:27.559
become a thousand here in the Congo.

00:11:27.559 --> 00:11:42.389
Brother Wakanga continues to serve as an elder at nearly 88 years old.

00:11:42.389 --> 00:11:47.389
Can you imagine yourself experiencing both the joys and difficulties he had

00:11:47.389 --> 00:11:50.389
as a circuit overseer?

00:11:50.389 --> 00:11:53.389
He courageously visited the Kitawala religious groups

00:11:53.389 --> 00:11:56.389
who claimed to serve Jehovah.

00:11:56.389 --> 00:12:01.389
Only to find some were violent and practiced immorality.

00:12:01.389 --> 00:12:04.389
But it was his reliance on Jehovah,

00:12:04.389 --> 00:12:09.389
and watching him turn the small group of brothers into more than 200,000

00:12:09.389 --> 00:12:11.389
that has kept him going.

00:12:11.389 --> 00:12:16.990
He personally experienced our theme for this program,

00:12:16.990 --> 00:12:22.590
the privilege and blessing of being God's fellow worker.

00:12:22.590 --> 00:12:28.590
As Jehovah's People, we enjoy many undeserved and precious privileges.

00:12:28.590 --> 00:12:34.590
Among them, we bear Jehovah's name and render him sacred service.

00:12:34.590 --> 00:12:40.590
As we carry out his will, he dignifies us in a very special way.

00:12:40.590 --> 00:12:46.590
At 1 Corinthians 3.9, the Apostle Paul under inspiration stated

00:12:46.590 --> 00:12:51.590
that we are God's fellow workers.

00:12:51.590 --> 00:12:55.590
What an honor to be a fellow worker with the universal sovereign

00:12:55.590 --> 00:12:58.590
our loving Heavenly Father.

00:12:58.590 --> 00:13:02.590
To build appreciation for the privilege of working with Jehovah,

00:13:02.590 --> 00:13:07.590
we're going to review events in the life of Jonathan, son of King Saul.

00:13:07.590 --> 00:13:12.590
1 Samuel 14.45 describes Jonathan when it says,

00:13:12.590 --> 00:13:16.590
for it was with God that he acted this day.

00:13:16.590 --> 00:13:20.590
What was the background that led to this statement?

00:13:20.590 --> 00:13:24.590
How did Jonathan act or work with Jehovah on that day?

00:13:25.590 --> 00:13:29.590
What lessons can we learn from their working relationship?

00:13:29.590 --> 00:13:33.590
And what blessings result from being a fellow worker with God?

00:13:33.590 --> 00:13:38.899
Let us begin with some background.

00:13:38.899 --> 00:13:44.899
1 Samuel 12 and verse 20 records the encouraging words spoken

00:13:44.899 --> 00:13:48.899
by the prophet Samuel to the nation of Israel.

00:13:48.899 --> 00:13:50.899
Do not be afraid.

00:13:50.899 --> 00:13:53.899
Only do not turn away from following Jehovah

00:13:53.899 --> 00:13:56.899
and serve Jehovah with all your heart.

00:13:56.899 --> 00:13:58.899
Verse 22 adds,

00:13:58.899 --> 00:14:01.899
for the sake of his great name,

00:14:01.899 --> 00:14:04.899
Jehovah will not abandon his people.

00:14:04.899 --> 00:14:06.899
As long as they remain faithful,

00:14:06.899 --> 00:14:12.899
Jehovah would always be there to guide, protect, and rescue them.

00:14:12.899 --> 00:14:16.899
These words no doubt strengthen Jonathan to carry out Jehovah's directive

00:14:16.899 --> 00:14:21.899
to subdue the enemy nations and take possession of the Promised Land.

00:14:21.899 --> 00:14:26.179
At 1 Samuel 13,

00:14:26.179 --> 00:14:29.179
we read that Jonathan was assigned 1000 men

00:14:29.179 --> 00:14:33.179
to attack a Philistine garrison at Giba.

00:14:33.179 --> 00:14:38.179
Although poorly equipped, Jonathan and his men succeeded.

00:14:38.179 --> 00:14:42.179
This victory strengthened Jonathan's confidence in Jehovah

00:14:42.179 --> 00:14:46.179
and provides a valuable lesson for us.

00:14:46.179 --> 00:14:48.179
While we gained strength and courage

00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:51.179
from Jehovah's reassuring words in the scriptures,

00:14:51.179 --> 00:14:55.179
our confidence in Jehovah's support becomes even stronger

00:14:55.179 --> 00:14:58.179
when we successfully carry out our assignments

00:14:58.179 --> 00:15:00.179
that may seem overwhelming.

00:15:00.179 --> 00:15:04.500
The account then relates how the Philistines

00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:06.500
were infuriated over their defeat

00:15:06.500 --> 00:15:09.500
and mounted a massive counterattack.

00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:11.500
They sent out raiding parties

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:14.500
from their camp at McMash near Jerusalem.

00:15:14.500 --> 00:15:17.500
Many as light men hid out of fear

00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:21.500
and some even fled to the other side of the Jordan River.

00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:27.500
In contrast, Jonathan remained courageous.

00:15:27.500 --> 00:15:29.500
Determined to put a stop to the raids,

00:15:29.500 --> 00:15:32.500
he confronted the Philistine outpost

00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:35.500
at the ravine pass of McMash.

00:15:35.500 --> 00:15:38.500
The approach was by way of a deep gorge

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:41.500
with nearly vertical cliffs.

00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:43.500
This would have seen next to impossible

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:46.500
to someone unfamiliar with the area.

00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:48.500
But Jonathan grew up in this territory

00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:50.500
and apparently knew it well.

00:15:50.500 --> 00:15:53.870
His knowledge of the surroundings

00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:56.870
provides another practical lesson.

00:15:56.870 --> 00:15:59.870
Whatever theocratic assignment we may be given,

00:15:59.870 --> 00:16:02.870
putting forth time and effort to get to know

00:16:02.870 --> 00:16:04.870
that the terrain, so to speak,

00:16:04.870 --> 00:16:07.870
will contribute to our effectiveness.

00:16:07.870 --> 00:16:09.870
When we show interest in our assigned work,

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:13.870
we become even more effective fellow workers of Jehovah.

00:16:13.870 --> 00:16:17.149
Let's read as Jonathan prepares

00:16:17.149 --> 00:16:21.399
to take action against the Philistines.

00:16:21.399 --> 00:16:24.399
First Samuel 146 states,

00:16:24.399 --> 00:16:26.399
so Jonathan said to his armor bearer,

00:16:26.399 --> 00:16:29.399
come and let us cross over to the outpost

00:16:29.399 --> 00:16:31.399
of these uncircumcized men.

00:16:31.399 --> 00:16:34.399
Perhaps Jehovah will act in our behalf

00:16:34.399 --> 00:16:36.399
for nothing can hinder Jehovah

00:16:36.399 --> 00:16:39.399
from saving by many or by few.

00:16:39.399 --> 00:16:43.399
What contributed to his confidence in Jehovah?

