Recall that he put faith

00:16:45.399 --> 00:16:47.399
in Jehovah's reassuring words

00:16:47.399 --> 00:16:49.399
to the prophet Samuel.

00:16:49.399 --> 00:16:51.399
Do not be afraid.

00:16:51.399 --> 00:16:53.399
For the sake of his great name,

00:16:53.399 --> 00:16:57.399
Jehovah will not abandon his people.

00:16:57.399 --> 00:16:59.399
He experienced Jehovah's support

00:16:59.399 --> 00:17:03.399
when he struck down the Philistine garrison at Giba.

00:17:03.399 --> 00:17:07.400
Jonathan could also think back on Israel's history.

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:09.400
He could reflect on how Gideon

00:17:09.400 --> 00:17:11.400
and his 300 men were victorious

00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:16.400
over 135,000 Midianites.

00:17:16.400 --> 00:17:18.400
He could meditate on Samson

00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:20.400
killing 1,000 Philistines

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:24.400
with the jawbone of a donkey.

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:27.400
Such examples would bolster his confidence

00:17:27.400 --> 00:17:31.400
that he was working with the Almighty God, Jehovah.

00:17:31.400 --> 00:17:35.839
We too can meditate on fellow workers of God

00:17:35.839 --> 00:17:37.839
recorded in the scriptures,

00:17:37.839 --> 00:17:39.839
as well as published life stories

00:17:39.839 --> 00:17:42.839
of modern-day faithful servants.

00:17:42.839 --> 00:17:45.839
Such examples reinforce our faith in Jehovah

00:17:45.839 --> 00:17:50.410
as we rely on him for success.

