I had the privilege for two years

00:20:36.940 --> 00:20:38.940
of sitting on the same table as sister Oram

00:20:38.940 --> 00:20:40.940
for morning worship.

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:41.940
She expected nothing

00:20:41.940 --> 00:20:44.940
and appreciated everything that you did for her.

00:20:44.940 --> 00:20:47.940
Sister Oram was affectionately known as Joy.

00:20:47.940 --> 00:20:50.940
And if you take the eith out of Joy,

00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:53.940
you left with the English word Joy,

00:20:53.940 --> 00:20:54.940
and that's under it.

00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:57.940
My impression of Joy when I first met her

00:20:57.940 --> 00:20:59.940
was here as this frail old lady.

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:02.940
But then when you got started to speak to Joy,

00:21:02.940 --> 00:21:05.940
you were tapping into a tremendous depth.

00:21:05.940 --> 00:21:08.940
About the age of 20, around about that time,

00:21:08.940 --> 00:21:10.940
I had the heavenly calling.

00:21:10.940 --> 00:21:12.940
That was a big battle.

00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:14.940
I couldn't understand why Joy Hoover

00:21:14.940 --> 00:21:16.940
would use a person like me.

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:18.940
When I was 21,

00:21:18.940 --> 00:21:21.940
I got into pioneering in 1939.

00:21:21.940 --> 00:21:23.940
But the police were after me

00:21:23.940 --> 00:21:25.940
because I wouldn't join the armed forces.

00:21:25.940 --> 00:21:27.940
And I was tried under a new act

00:21:27.940 --> 00:21:29.940
and they kept taking me to a side room

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:30.940
and saying,

00:21:30.940 --> 00:21:31.940
if you will see,

00:21:31.940 --> 00:21:33.940
you're not connected with Joy Hoover's witnesses.

00:21:33.940 --> 00:21:35.940
Not connected with the watchtower,

00:21:35.940 --> 00:21:36.940
you have a walkaway.

00:21:36.940 --> 00:21:38.940
I said, I am connected with the watchtower.

00:21:38.940 --> 00:21:41.940
I'm proud to be connected with the watchtower.

00:21:41.940 --> 00:21:42.940
They said,

00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:43.940
then they are direct to you.

00:21:43.940 --> 00:21:44.940
I said, no,

00:21:44.940 --> 00:21:46.940
my stand of not doing as you wish.

00:21:46.940 --> 00:21:48.940
It's my own personal stand.

00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:49.940
So this went on.

00:21:49.940 --> 00:21:50.940
In the end,

00:21:50.940 --> 00:21:52.940
they sent me to prison just for two months

00:21:52.940 --> 00:21:53.940
and let me out.

00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:55.940
I partnered with another sister.

00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:58.940
And she and I went to Northern Ireland

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:00.940
and pioneered there for 18 months.

00:22:00.940 --> 00:22:01.940
And it was in Northern Ireland.

00:22:01.940 --> 00:22:03.940
We had our call to Gilead.

00:22:03.940 --> 00:22:06.940
In 1948, Joy was invited to Gilead.

00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:08.940
And that was the 11th class.

00:22:08.940 --> 00:22:10.940
It left an impression on me,

00:22:10.940 --> 00:22:12.940
which I will never, ever, ever forget.

00:22:12.940 --> 00:22:15.940
You pick up that spirit of good behaviour, of love.

00:22:15.940 --> 00:22:17.940
It's something that leaves its mark,

00:22:17.940 --> 00:22:18.940
or it should do.

00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:21.940
It has left its mark on me very, very much so.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:22.940
One thing, rather,

00:22:22.940 --> 00:22:24.940
nor impressed on us,

00:22:24.940 --> 00:22:26.940
you'll be three years on your assignment

00:22:26.940 --> 00:22:28.940
before you really love it.

00:22:28.940 --> 00:22:29.940
And it was true,

00:22:29.940 --> 00:22:31.940
because it was a hard assignment.

00:22:31.940 --> 00:22:32.940
After Gilead,

00:22:32.940 --> 00:22:34.940
she was assigned to be a missionary in Dublin

00:22:34.940 --> 00:22:36.940
in the Irish Republic.

00:22:36.940 --> 00:22:37.940
That was the time

00:22:37.940 --> 00:22:40.940
when Catholic priests used to organise mobs

00:22:40.940 --> 00:22:42.940
against the pioneers.

00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:43.940
She was full of joy,

00:22:43.940 --> 00:22:45.940
but that didn't mean to say she'd had an easy life.

00:22:45.940 --> 00:22:47.940
You never went out from door to door

00:22:47.940 --> 00:22:49.940
without being mobs and attacked

00:22:49.940 --> 00:22:51.940
and beaten up and thrown around.

00:22:51.940 --> 00:22:54.940
And you could only do a few houses in a road

00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:56.940
and you have to get away very quickly.

00:22:56.940 --> 00:22:58.940
But we made a very good name.

00:22:58.940 --> 00:23:00.940
People got to know we were completely neutral.

00:23:00.940 --> 00:23:03.940
They chose four of us to work the business property.

00:23:03.940 --> 00:23:06.940
And I got some studies going in their offices.

00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:08.940
But one place I went into,

00:23:08.940 --> 00:23:10.940
I walked the length of this draper shop.

00:23:10.940 --> 00:23:12.940
And I asked if I could

00:23:12.940 --> 00:23:13.940
go into the manager's office.

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:14.940
And as I went in,

00:23:14.940 --> 00:23:16.940
I didn't say a word.

00:23:16.940 --> 00:23:17.940
I didn't owe my mouth

00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:18.940
and even say good morning,

00:23:18.940 --> 00:23:19.940
but this man stood up

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:20.940
and he said,

00:23:20.940 --> 00:23:21.940
rust the light!

00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:23.940
And he took hold of me

00:23:23.940 --> 00:23:24.940
by the scruff of my neck

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:25.940
and the seat of my pants

00:23:25.940 --> 00:23:26.940
and he lifted me up.

00:23:26.940 --> 00:23:27.940
And he carried me

00:23:27.940 --> 00:23:29.940
the length of the store.

00:23:29.940 --> 00:23:31.940
Well, like a silly one,

00:23:31.940 --> 00:23:34.940
I should have gone heavy on him, you see.

00:23:34.940 --> 00:23:35.940
But instead of that,

00:23:35.940 --> 00:23:36.940
I lit my legs paddled.

00:23:36.940 --> 00:23:38.940
And I was hanging on to my book bag

00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:39.940
not wanting to lose it.

00:23:39.940 --> 00:23:41.940
And when he got to the front door,

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:42.940
the staff,

00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:44.940
their eyes were absolutely gone.

00:23:44.940 --> 00:23:45.940
What's happening?

00:23:45.940 --> 00:23:46.940
He opened his front door

00:23:46.940 --> 00:23:47.940
and he threw me out of the tree

00:23:47.940 --> 00:23:48.940
and I went,

00:23:48.940 --> 00:23:49.940
zoom!

00:23:49.940 --> 00:23:50.940
And just my little zoom again.

00:23:50.940 --> 00:23:52.940
And one of the brothers

00:23:52.940 --> 00:23:54.940
was passing and he caught me.

00:23:54.940 --> 00:23:56.940
And caught me steady.

00:23:56.940 --> 00:23:57.940
So it was going on.

00:23:57.940 --> 00:23:59.940
And I couldn't stop laughing.

00:23:59.940 --> 00:24:00.940
To me,

00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:01.940
it was very, very funny.

00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:03.940
The rest was so crossed about it.

00:24:03.940 --> 00:24:04.940
But I wasn't a store cross.

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:06.940
I thought it was quite hilarious.

00:24:06.940 --> 00:24:09.940
I could see myself being carried through this shop.

00:24:09.940 --> 00:24:10.940
Sky high.

00:24:10.940 --> 00:24:11.940
Things like that happened.

00:24:11.940 --> 00:24:14.940
These experiences did not dampen her zeal.

00:24:14.940 --> 00:24:17.940
She always retained that missionary spirit.

00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:19.940
I first met Joey

00:24:19.940 --> 00:24:21.940
when I was commuting to Bethel in the infirmary.

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:24.940
She was sitting on that old fashioned chair

00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:26.940
with this huge Bible

00:24:26.940 --> 00:24:28.940
and she stayed there

00:24:28.940 --> 00:24:30.940
hours reading the Bible,

00:24:30.940 --> 00:24:31.940
praying to Yelva.

00:24:31.940 --> 00:24:33.940
Often when you came in,

00:24:33.940 --> 00:24:35.940
she'd been in the middle of Bible reading

00:24:35.940 --> 00:24:36.940
and she'd be saying something like,

00:24:36.940 --> 00:24:38.940
Daniel's just been thrown into the line's den.

00:24:38.940 --> 00:24:40.940
Or, oh, Yelva's really angry.

00:24:40.940 --> 00:24:42.940
He's thundering from the heavens.

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:43.940
And it made me think,

00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:45.940
wow, she must have read the Bible so many times.

00:24:45.940 --> 00:24:47.940
But every time it was as if

00:24:47.940 --> 00:24:49.940
it was happening right in front of her.

00:24:49.940 --> 00:24:52.940
Right up until she became incapacitated,

00:24:52.940 --> 00:24:54.940
she was conducting Bible studies

00:24:54.940 --> 00:24:57.940
and helping people to come to know Yelva.

00:24:57.940 --> 00:25:00.940
She was looking forward to her heavenly reward.

00:25:00.940 --> 00:25:02.940
And for her that was

00:25:02.940 --> 00:25:05.940
the culmination of a life of joy in Yelva's service

00:25:05.940 --> 00:25:07.940
and that she was just transferring

00:25:07.940 --> 00:25:09.940
to her next assignment.

00:25:09.940 --> 00:25:11.940
I'm very, very grateful for work.

00:25:11.940 --> 00:25:13.940
In fact, often in my prayers,

00:25:13.940 --> 00:25:16.940
pray to Yelva that I'll have some good work to do today.

00:25:16.940 --> 00:25:26.400
I'm very grateful to have work to do.

00:25:26.400 --> 00:25:28.400
Similar to what we learned about Jonathan,

00:25:28.400 --> 00:25:33.400
Sister Orham demonstrated humble reliance on Yelva.

00:25:33.400 --> 00:25:35.400
So sure was her trust in God

00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:38.400
that she could face even fearful situations

00:25:38.400 --> 00:25:41.400
with a sense of humor.

00:25:41.400 --> 00:25:44.400
We may not be able to laugh when enduring persecution,

00:25:44.400 --> 00:25:50.400
but we can imitate Joy's faith and firm resolve.

00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:55.000
What else can we learn from Jonathan's account?

00:25:55.000 --> 00:25:59.000
Picking up at 1 Samuel 1412,

00:25:59.000 --> 00:26:04.000
Jonathan and his armor bearer advanced toward the Philistines.

00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:06.000
From their elevated location,

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:09.000
the Philistines shout to them.

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:13.000
Come up to us, and we will teach you a lesson.

00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:16.000
At once, Jonathan said to his armor bearer,

00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:21.000
follow me, for Jehovah will give them into the hand of Israel.

00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:26.000
Jonathan had requested a specific sign, and he got it.

00:26:26.000 --> 00:26:30.000
But it meant advancing up a steep and treacherous incline

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:33.000
right into the enemy hands.

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:37.000
Someone lacking complete trust in Jehovah might have said,

00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:39.000
before proceeding,

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:42.000
or perhaps we should ask for another sign,

00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:44.000
but not Jonathan.

00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:47.000
Without hesitation, he told his attendant to follow him

00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:52.000
because Jehovah would give the enemy into their hand.

00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:54.000
When we received Jehovah's direction,

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:56.000
we should, without hesitation,

00:26:56.000 --> 00:26:58.000
put our hearts into the work,

00:26:58.000 --> 00:27:00.000
confident of Jehovah's backing.

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:03.380
What happened next?

